Exercise 3 - Simple Spring Boot REST Controller

📄 Description:
This exercise demonstrates the creation of a basic REST API using Spring Boot. A controller is created to respond with a welcome message at a specific endpoint.

🧪 Sample Input:
GET request to:
http://localhost:8080/welcome

✅ Output:
Welcome to Spring Boot!


⚙️ What’s Used:
- `@RestController` for creating REST API
- `@GetMapping` for defining GET endpoint
- Spring Boot embedded Tomcat server (port 8080)
- Java 17 + Spring Boot 3.5.3
